HEADWORD: Propidene
<hw>Pro"pi*dene</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Prop</ets>yl
+ ethyl<ets>idene</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>The
unsymmetrical hypothetical hydrocarbon radical,
<chform>CH3.CH2.CH</chform>, analogous to ethylidene, and regarded as
the type of certain derivatives of propane; -- called also
<altname>propylidene</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
